assessment_details.task_description:
This assessment provides students with an opportunity to apply the understanding developed in the course to the practical analysis of an organisation's HR strategy. In groups of 3 to 5, students will conduct an analysis of an organisation's HR strategy and policy on the basis of the HR literature focussing on one (1) relevant area, such as;

Bullying, discrimination and harassment

Talent management

Succession planning

Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR).

The report should be between 3500 and 4000 words, excluding references and appendices. The following aspects should be included in the analysis:
What the organisation does - describe the task of the organisation, that is what they do, their mission;

The organisation's HRM strategy and policies - identify and describe what activities the organisation uses and how they use them to organise and manage their employees for performing tasks effectively;

Critical evaluation - conduct a critical evaluation of the organisation's HR strategy and policies based on the literature;

Recommendations - with the above analysis as the basis, provide suggestions of how the selected organisation can improve their HR strategy and policies.

In preparing this report, students should consult the Business School's Assignment Writing Handbook that is available in the Resources section of the Business School Postgraduate Coursework Community blackboard site. The Schools preferred referencing style is Harvard (see www.library.uq.edu.au/training/citation/harvard.html ). Note that group memberships will be determined by week 3.
